## Coordination with Other Agents

More than one agent may work this repo. To avoid conflict:

- {% if include_project_context %}Treat `project-context.md` as the shared handoff document.{% else %}Keep a shared handoff note and read it at session start.{% endif %}
- Do not assume the working tree reflects only your prior changes — check
  `git status` and `git log` before editing.
- Prefer clear task ownership before parallel work; avoid editing the same
  files as another agent unless explicitly asked.
{% endif %}
## Durable Memory

Durable facts, decisions, and landmines live in `.claude/memory/` as one-fact
files (frontmatter: `name`, `description`, `metadata.type`; linked with
`[[slug]]`). When something becomes durable, add a one-fact file and a line in
`.claude/memory/MEMORY.md` — do not bury it in {% if include_project_context %}`project-context.md`{% else %}prose{% endif %}.

